description:
The mark of the beast has been a hot topic for centuries. Will it be a microchip in the wrist, a universal ID card, or a hidden DNA marker in a vaccine? What is it really? Does the Bible have insight into this provocative question?

‚ÄúThe Mark‚Äù will provide a clear answer to this with an intriguing study on Revelation 13 and the topic of the Mark of the Beast. What is the mark? Does anyone have it now? How can it be avoided?

This is the 10th episode in the AWR Master Class series called Unlocking Bible Prophecies. You can follow the series and interact LIVE at:

https://bible.awr.org/the-mark/

ABOUT CAMI OETMAN
Ten years ago, Cami Oetman had a real encounter with God that would change her life forever. She was a successful entrepreneur at the time, and the transition wasn't easy. However, the truth Cami will share in this series was so compelling that she knew every human being in the world should experience the love of Jesus as she had.

Within three years, she had preached 350 Bible presentations. Today, as a vice president for Adventist World Radio, Cami travels the world documenting the miracles that take place when people give their hearts to Jesus.

It may seem difficult to imagine yourself understanding Bible prophecy. Cami couldn‚Äôt either. She had spent two decades in the modeling world‚Äîin front of and behind the camera. She had also used her master‚Äôs degree in social work to care for hospice patients. She then started a successful retail business. But no one can predict how they will react when they have a real experience with God!

THE MARK
What is this mysterious Mark of the Beast? Who is the beast in the book of Revelation? Is it symbolic? And what does the number 666 really mean?

The good news is that Bible prophecy provides clear answers to these important questions. You'll want to pay close attention in this episode‚Äôs look into "The Mark."

In Revelation 13, the Apostle John writes that there are only two groups of people living on earth when Jesus Christ returns. There is the faithful group that worships God and has received His seal. And then there are those who worship the beast and receive a mark on their right hands or on their foreheads. 

Thankfully, the Bible reveals what the Mark of the Beast is while revealing the identity of the beast. 

This beast of Revelation 13 is described as a worldwide religious and political power that would rule for 1,260 years. During this time, the beast would claim to be God and have the power to forgive sins. Anyone who wouldn‚Äôt worship the beast would be persecuted, even to death.
